{
  "text": "Numerical calculations show that the trajectory for (16) is always on a closed curve, as in case of (11), independently of parameter values. Therefore, the general form of discrete population dynamics given by (16) can be regarded as dynamically consistent with the Lotka-Volterra prey-predator system [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "117771948"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "117771948": {
      "title": "Discrete competitive and cooperative models of Lotka-Volterra type",
      "abstract": "The dynamics of discrete Lotka\u2013Volterra system of two species is investigated. It is shown that the proposed discrete models for competitive and cooperative systems possess \u201cdynamical consistency\u201d with their continuous counterparts."
    }
  }
}